        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 3:31AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 330 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Malaquite Beach, or 20 miles south of Corpus Christi,
moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Malaquite Beach and Padre Balli Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
